Summary: Backup directories using HTTP and CDRs
Name: @NAME@
Version: @VERSION@
Release: @RELEASE@
Copyright: @COPYRIGHT@
Vendor: @VENDOR@
Group: System Environment/Base
Source: %{name}-%{version}.tar.gz
Buildroot: @VAR@/tmp/%{name}-buildroot
BuildArchitectures: noarch
Requires: rocks-pylib


%package server
Summary: CGI Script
Group: System Environment/Base

%description server

Web based serice to backup a system

%package client
Summary: Client side
Group: System Environment/Base

%description client

Client tools to remotely build an ISO image of a directory tree.

%description
Tools to help backup a system over http and onto CDs.

##
## PREP
##
%prep
%setup

##
## BUILD
##
%build
make build

##
## INSTALL
##
%install
make ROOT=$RPM_BUILD_ROOT install

##
## FILES
#
%files server
/var/www

%files client
/opt/rocks
/etc

##
## CLEAN
##
%clean
/bin/rm -rf $RPM_BUILD_ROOT
